{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/buildingamacosvmmanager"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Building a macOS VM Manager","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This article walks through the layered structure of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Spooktacular SwiftUI app so you can build something comparable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without repeating the architectural decisions we already settled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app target depends on three Swift packages in this repo:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SpookCore"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — pure Swift domain types. No AppKit, no","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization"},{"text":", no networking. Use it for models, enums,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and protocol “ports” that describe what the app needs without","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"committing to a concrete transport.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SpookApplication"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — use cases and services that combine"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain types into workflows (RBAC evaluation, tenant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"isolation, runner-pool orchestration)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"SpookInfrastructureApple","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":" — Apple-framework adapters.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Wraps ","type":"text"},{"code":"VZVirtualMachine","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSPasteboard","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSWorkspace","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Security.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Network.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Views stay thin: they observe "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Observable"},{"type":"text","text":" state objects and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call through to these libraries. Keeping logic out of views is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"what makes the same codebase ship a CLI, a Kubernetes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controller, and an App Store binary from one package."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Compose the Spooktacular libraries into a first-class Mac app."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BuildingAMacOSVMManager","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"title":"SpooktacularKit","abstract":[{"text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"},"doc://SpooktacularKit